<usx version="2.0">
    <book code="PRO" style="id">The Book of Proverbs</book>
    <para style="mt">The Book of Proverbs</para>
    <chapter number="1" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Beginning of Knowledge</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />The <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 4:32; Prov. 10:1; 25:1; Eccl. 12:9</char></note>proverbs of Solomon the son of David, king of Israel:</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />To know wisdom and instruction,</para>
	<para style="q2">To perceive the words of understanding,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />To receive the instruction of wisdom,</para>
	<para style="q2">Justice, judgment, and equity;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />To give prudence to the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 9:4</char></note>simple,</para>
	<para style="q2">To the young man knowledge and discretion—</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 9:9</char></note>A wise <char style="it">man</char> will hear and increase learning,</para>
	<para style="q2">And a man of understanding will attain wise counsel,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />To understand a proverb and an enigma,</para>
	<para style="q2">The words of the wise and their <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 12:8; Ps. 78:2; Dan. 8:23</char></note>riddles.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 28:28; Ps. 111:10; Prov. 9:10; 15:33; (Eccl. 12:13)</char></note>The fear of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> the beginning of knowledge,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> fools despise wisdom and instruction.</para>
	<para style="s">Shun Evil Counsel</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 4:1</char></note>My son, hear the instruction of your father,</para>
	<para style="q2">And do not forsake the law of your mother;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />For they <char style="it">will</char> <char style="it">be</char> a <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 3:22</char></note>graceful ornament on your head,</para>
	<para style="q2">And chains about your neck.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />My son, if sinners entice you,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 39:7–10; Deut. 13:8; Ps. 50:18; (Eph. 5:11)</char></note>Do not consent.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />If they say, “Come with us,</para>
	<para style="q2">Let us <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 12:6; Jer. 5:26</char></note>lie in wait to <char style="it">shed</char> blood;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let us lurk secretly for the innocent without cause;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Let us swallow them alive like Sheol,</para>
	<para style="q2">And whole, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 28:1</char></note>like those who go down to the Pit;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />We shall find all <char style="it">kinds</char> of precious possessions,</para>
	<para style="q2">We shall fill our houses with spoil;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />Cast in your lot among us,</para>
	<para style="q2">Let us all have one purse”—</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />My son, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 1:1; Prov. 4:14</char></note>do not walk in the way with them,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:101</char></note>Keep your foot from their path;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 6:17, 18; (Is. 59:7); Rom. 3:15</char></note>For their feet run to evil,</para>
	<para style="q2">And they make haste to shed blood.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />Surely, in vain the net is spread</para>
	<para style="q2">In the sight of any bird;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />But they lie in wait for their <char style="it">own</char> blood,</para>
	<para style="q2">They lurk secretly for their <char style="it">own</char> lives.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 15:27; (1 Tim. 6:10)</char></note>So <char style="it">are</char> the ways of everyone who is greedy for gain;</para>
	<para style="q2">It takes away the life of its owners.</para>
	<para style="s">The Call of Wisdom</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 8:1; 9:3; (John 7:37)</char></note>Wisdom calls aloud outside;</para>
	<para style="q2">She raises her voice in the open squares.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />She cries out in the chief concourses,</para>
	<para style="q2">At the openings of the gates in the city</para>
	<para style="q2">She speaks her words:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />“How long, you simple ones, will you love simplicity?</para>
	<para style="q2">For scorners delight in their scorning,</para>
	<para style="q2">And fools hate knowledge.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" />Turn at my rebuke;</para>
	<para style="q2">Surely <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 32:15; Joel 2:28; (John 7:39)</char></note>I will pour out my spirit on you;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will make my words known to you.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 65:12; 66:4; Jer. 7:13; Zech. 7:11</char></note>Because I have called and you refused,</para>
	<para style="q2">I have stretched out my hand and no one regarded,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" />Because you <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 107:11; Luke 7:30</char></note>disdained all my counsel,</para>
	<para style="q2">And would have none of my rebuke,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 2:4</char></note>I also will laugh at your calamity;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will mock when your terror comes,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" />When <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 10:24, 25)</char></note>your terror comes like a storm,</para>
	<para style="q2">And your destruction comes like a whirlwind,</para>
	<para style="q2">When distress and anguish come upon you.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="28" style="v" />“Then<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 8:18; Job 27:9; 35:12; Ps. 18:41; Is. 1:15; Jer. 11:11; 14:12; Ezek. 8:18; Mic. 3:4; Zech. 7:13; (James 4:3)</char></note> they will call on me, but I will not answer;</para>
	<para style="q2">They will seek me diligently, but they will not find me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="29" style="v" />Because they <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 21:14; Prov. 1:22</char></note>hated knowledge</para>
	<para style="q2">And did not <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:173</char></note>choose the fear of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="30" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 81:11; Prov. 1:25</char></note>They would have none of my counsel</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> despised my every rebuke.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="31" style="v" />Therefore <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 4:8; Prov. 5:22, 23; 22:8; Is. 3:11; Jer. 6:19</char></note>they shall eat the fruit of their own way,</para>
	<para style="q2">And be filled to the full with their own fancies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="32" style="v" />For the turning away of the simple will slay them,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the complacency of fools will destroy them;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="33" style="v" />But whoever listens to me will dwell <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 3:24–26</char></note>safely,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 112:7</char></note>will be secure, without fear of evil.”</para>
	<chapter number="2" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Value of Wisdom</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />My son, if you receive my words,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 4:21)</char></note>treasure my commands within you,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />So that you incline your ear to wisdom,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> apply your heart to understanding;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Yes, if you cry out for discernment,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> lift up your voice for understanding,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 3:14)</char></note>If you seek her as silver,</para>
	<para style="q2">And search for her as <char style="it">for</char> hidden treasures;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(James 1:5, 6)</char></note>Then you will understand the fear of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And find the knowledge of God.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 3:9, 12; (Job 32:8; James 1:5)</char></note>For the <char style="sc">Lord</char> gives wisdom;</para>
	<para style="q2">From His mouth <char style="it">come</char> knowledge and understanding;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />He stores up sound wisdom for the upright;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 84:11); Prov. 30:5</char></note><char style="it">He</char> <char style="it">is</char> a shield to those who walk uprightly;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />He guards the paths of justice,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Sam. 2:9); Ps. 66:9</char></note>preserves the way of His saints.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Then you will understand righteousness and justice,</para>
	<para style="q2">Equity <char style="it">and</char> every good path.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />When wisdom enters your heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">And knowledge is pleasant to your soul,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Discretion will preserve you;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 4:6; 6:22</char></note>Understanding will keep you,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />To deliver you from the way of evil,</para>
	<para style="q2">From the man who speaks perverse things,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />From those who leave the paths of uprightness</para>
	<para style="q2">To <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 82:5; Prov. 4:19; (John 3:19, 20)</char></note>walk in the ways of darkness;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:23; Jer. 11:15; (Rom. 1:32)</char></note>Who rejoice in doing evil,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> delight in the perversity of the wicked;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 125:5; (Prov. 21:8)</char></note>Whose ways <char style="it">are</char> crooked,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">who</char> <char style="it">are</char> devious in their paths;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />To deliver you from <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 5:20; 6:24; 7:5</char></note>the immoral woman,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 5:3</char></note>From the seductress <char style="it">who</char> flatters with her words,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />Who forsakes the companion of her youth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And forgets the covenant of her God.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 7:27</char></note>her house leads down to death,</para>
	<para style="q2">And her paths to the dead;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />None who go to her return,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor do they regain the paths of life—</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />So you may walk in the way of goodness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And keep <char style="it">to</char> the paths of righteousness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />For the upright will dwell in the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:3</char></note>land,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the blameless will remain in it;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />But the wicked will be cut off from the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the unfaithful will be uprooted from it.</para>
	<chapter number="3" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Guidance for the Young</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />My son, do not forget my law,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 8:1</char></note>But let your heart keep my commands;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />For length of days and long life</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:165; Prov. 4:10</char></note>peace they will add to you.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />Let not mercy and truth forsake you;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 13:9; Deut. 6:8; Prov. 6:21</char></note>Bind them around your neck,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 7:3; Jer. 17:1; (2 Cor. 3:3)</char></note>Write them on the tablet of your heart,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 2:26; Luke 2:52; Rom. 14:18</char></note><char style="it">And</char> so find favor and high esteem</para>
	<para style="q2">In the sight of God and man.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 37:3, 5); Prov. 22:19</char></note>Trust in the <char style="sc">Lord</char> with all your heart,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 23:4; (Jer. 9:23, 24)</char></note>And lean not on your own understanding;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Chr. 28:9); Prov. 16:3; (Phil. 4:6; James 1:5)</char></note>In all your ways acknowledge Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He shall direct your paths.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />Do not be wise in your own <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rom. 12:16</char></note>eyes;</para>
	<para style="q2">Fear the <char style="sc">Lord</char> and depart from evil.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />It will be health to your flesh,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 21:24</char></note>strength to your bones.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 22:29; Deut. 26:2; (Mal. 3:10)</char></note>Honor the <char style="sc">Lord</char> with your possessions,</para>
	<para style="q2">And with the firstfruits of all your increase;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 28:8</char></note>So your barns will be filled with plenty,</para>
	<para style="q2">And your vats will overflow with new wine.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 5:17; Ps. 94:12; Heb. 12:5, 6; Rev. 3:19</char></note>My son, do not despise the chastening of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor detest His correction;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />For whom the <char style="sc">Lord</char> loves He corrects,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 8:5; Prov. 13:24</char></note>Just as a father the son <char style="it">in</char> <char style="it">whom</char> he delights.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 8:32, 34, 35</char></note>Happy <char style="it">is</char> the man <char style="it">who</char> finds wisdom,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the man <char style="it">who</char> gains understanding;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 28:13</char></note>For her proceeds <char style="it">are</char> better than the profits of silver,</para>
	<para style="q2">And her gain than fine gold.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />She <char style="it">is</char> more precious than rubies,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 13:44</char></note>all the things you may desire cannot compare with her.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 8:18; (1 Tim. 4:8)</char></note>Length of days <char style="it">is</char> in her right hand,</para>
	<para style="q2">In her left hand riches and honor.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 11:29)</char></note>Her ways <char style="it">are</char> ways of pleasantness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And all her paths <char style="it">are</char> peace.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />She <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 2:9; Prov. 11:30; 13:12; 15:4; Rev. 2:7</char></note>a tree of life to those who take hold of her,</para>
	<para style="q2">And happy <char style="it">are</char> <char style="it">all</char> who retain her.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 104:24; Prov. 8:27</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> by wisdom founded the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2">By understanding He established the heavens;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />By His knowledge the depths were <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 7:11</char></note>broken up,</para>
	<para style="q2">And clouds drop down the dew.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="21" style="v" />My son, let them not depart from your eyes—</para>
	<para style="q2">Keep sound wisdom and discretion;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />So they will be life to your soul</para>
	<para style="q2">And grace to your neck.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 37:24; 91:11, 12); Prov. 10:9</char></note>Then you will walk safely in your way,</para>
	<para style="q2">And your foot will not stumble.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" />When you lie down, you will not be afraid;</para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, you will lie down and your sleep will be sweet.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 91:5; 1 Pet. 3:14</char></note>Do not be afraid of sudden terror,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor of trouble from the wicked when it comes;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" />For the <char style="sc">Lord</char> will be your confidence,</para>
	<para style="q2">And will keep your foot from being caught.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rom. 13:7; (Gal. 6:10)</char></note>Do not withhold good from those to whom it is due,</para>
	<para style="q2">When it is in the power of your hand to do <char style="it">so.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 19:13; Deut. 24:15</char></note>Do not say to your neighbor,</para>
	<para style="q2">“Go, and come back,</para>
	<para style="q2">And tomorrow I will give <char style="it">it,</char>”</para>
	<para style="q2">When you have it with you.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="29" style="v" />Do not devise evil against your neighbor,</para>
	<para style="q2">For he dwells by you for safety’s sake.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="30" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 26:17; (Rom. 12:18)</char></note>Do not strive with a man without cause,</para>
	<para style="q2">If he has done you no harm.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="31" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:1; Prov. 24:1</char></note>Do not envy the oppressor,</para>
	<para style="q2">And choose none of his ways;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="32" style="v" />For the perverse <char style="it">person</char> <char style="it">is</char> an abomination to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 25:14</char></note>But His secret counsel <char style="it">is</char> with the upright.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="33" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 26:14, 16; Deut. 11:28; Zech. 5:3, 4; Mal. 2:2</char></note>The curse of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> on the house of the wicked,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 8:6; Ps. 1:3</char></note>He blesses the home of the just.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="34" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">James 4:6; 1 Pet. 5:5</char></note>Surely He scorns the scornful,</para>
	<para style="q2">But gives grace to the humble.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="35" style="v" />The wise shall inherit glory,</para>
	<para style="q2">But shame shall be the legacy of fools.</para>
	<chapter number="4" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Security in Wisdom</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Hear, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 34:11; Prov. 1:8</char></note><char style="it">my</char> children, the instruction of a father,</para>
	<para style="q2">And give attention to know understanding;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />For I give you good doctrine:</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not forsake my law.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />When I was my father’s son,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 29:1</char></note>Tender and the only one in the sight of my mother,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 28:9; Eph. 6:4</char></note>He also taught me, and said to me:</para>
	<para style="q2">“Let your heart retain my words;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 7:2</char></note>Keep my commands, and live.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 2:2, 3</char></note>Get wisdom! Get understanding!</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not forget, nor turn away from the words of my mouth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Do not forsake her, and she will preserve you;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Thess. 2:10</char></note>Love her, and she will keep you.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 3:13, 14; Matt. 13:44</char></note>Wisdom <char style="it">is</char> the principal thing;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Therefore</char> get wisdom.</para>
	<para style="q2">And in all your getting, get understanding.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 2:30</char></note>Exalt her, and she will promote you;</para>
	<para style="q2">She will bring you honor, when you embrace her.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />She will place on your head <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 3:22</char></note>an ornament of grace;</para>
	<para style="q2">A crown of glory she will deliver to you.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />Hear, my son, and receive my sayings,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 3:2</char></note>And the years of your life will be many.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />I have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 12:23</char></note>taught you in the way of wisdom;</para>
	<para style="q2">I have led you in right paths.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />When you walk, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 18:7; Ps. 18:36</char></note>your steps will not be hindered,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 91:11); Prov. 3:23</char></note>And when you run, you will not stumble.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />Take firm hold of instruction, do not let go;</para>
	<para style="q2">Keep her, for she <char style="it">is</char> your life.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 1:1; Prov. 1:15</char></note>Do not enter the path of the wicked,</para>
	<para style="q2">And do not walk in the way of evil.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />Avoid it, do not travel on it;</para>
	<para style="q2">Turn away from it and pass on.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 36:4; Mic. 2:1</char></note>For they do not sleep unless they have done evil;</para>
	<para style="q2">And their sleep is taken away unless they make <char style="it">someone</char> fall.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />For they eat the bread of wickedness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And drink the wine of violence.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 26:7; Matt. 5:14, 45; Phil. 2:15</char></note>But the path of the just <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 23:4</char></note><char style="it">is</char> like the shining sun,</para>
	<para style="q2">That shines ever brighter unto the perfect day.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 2:9; (Job 18:5, 6); Prov. 2:13; (Is. 59:9, 10; Jer. 23:12); John 12:35</char></note>The way of the wicked <char style="it">is</char> like darkness;</para>
	<para style="q2">They do not know what makes them stumble.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="20" style="v" />My son, give attention to my words;</para>
	<para style="q2">Incline your ear to my sayings.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />Do not let them depart from your eyes;</para>
	<para style="q2">Keep them in the midst of your heart;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />For they <char style="it">are</char> life to those who find them,</para>
	<para style="q2">And health to all their flesh.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" />Keep your heart with all diligence,</para>
	<para style="q2">For out of it <char style="it">spring</char> the issues of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 12:34; 15:18, 19; Mark 7:21; Luke 6:45)</char></note>life.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" />Put away from you a deceitful mouth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And put perverse lips far from you.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" />Let your eyes look straight ahead,</para>
	<para style="q2">And your eyelids look right before you.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" />Ponder the path of your <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 5:21; Heb. 12:13</char></note>feet,</para>
	<para style="q2">And let all your ways be established.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" />Do not turn to the right or the left;</para>
	<para style="q2">Remove your foot from evil.</para>
	<chapter number="5" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Peril of Adultery</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />My son, pay attention to my wisdom;</para>
	<para style="q2">Lend your ear to my understanding,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />That you may preserve discretion,</para>
	<para style="q2">And your lips <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Mal. 2:7</char></note>may keep knowledge.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 2:16</char></note>For the lips of an immoral woman drip honey,</para>
	<para style="q2">And her mouth <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 55:21</char></note>smoother than oil;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />But in the end she is bitter as wormwood,</para>
	<para style="q2">Sharp as a two-edged sword.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Her feet go down to death,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 7:27</char></note>Her steps lay hold of hell.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Lest you ponder <char style="it">her</char> path of life—</para>
	<para style="q2">Her ways are unstable;</para>
	<para style="q2">You do not know <char style="it">them.</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />Therefore hear me now, <char style="it">my</char> children,</para>
	<para style="q2">And do not depart from the words of my mouth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Remove your way far from her,</para>
	<para style="q2">And do not go near the door of her house,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Lest you give your honor to others,</para>
	<para style="q2">And your years to the cruel <char style="it">one;</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />Lest aliens be filled with your wealth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And your labors <char style="it">go</char> to the house of a foreigner;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />And you mourn at last,</para>
	<para style="q2">When your flesh and your body are consumed,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />And say:</para>
	<para style="q2">“How I have hated instruction,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my heart despised correction!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />I have not obeyed the voice of my teachers,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor inclined my ear to those who instructed me!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />I was on the verge of total ruin,</para>
	<para style="q2">In the midst of the assembly and congregation.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" />Drink water from your own cistern,</para>
	<para style="q2">And running water from your own well.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />Should your fountains be dispersed abroad,</para>
	<para style="q2">Streams of water in the streets?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />Let them be only your own,</para>
	<para style="q2">And not for strangers with you.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />Let your fountain be blessed,</para>
	<para style="q2">And rejoice with <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 24:5; Eccl. 9:9; Mal. 2:14</char></note>the wife of your youth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Song 2:9</char></note><char style="it">As</char> <char style="it">a</char> loving deer and a graceful doe,</para>
	<para style="q2">Let her breasts satisfy you at all times;</para>
	<para style="q2">And always be enraptured with her love.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />For why should you, my son, be enraptured by <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 2:16</char></note>an immoral woman,</para>
	<para style="q2">And be embraced in the arms of a seductress?</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="21" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Chr. 16:9; Job 31:4; 34:21; Prov. 15:3; Jer. 16:17; 32:19; Hos. 7:2; Heb. 4:13</char></note>For the ways of man <char style="it">are</char> before the eyes of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He ponders all his paths.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 32:23; Ps. 9:5; Prov. 1:31; Is. 3:11</char></note>His own iniquities entrap the wicked <char style="it">man,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">And he is caught in the cords of his sin.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 4:21</char></note>He shall die for lack of instruction,</para>
	<para style="q2">And in the greatness of his folly he shall go astray.</para>
	<chapter number="6" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Dangerous Promises</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />My son, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 11:15</char></note>if you become surety for your friend,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">If</char> you have shaken hands in pledge for a stranger,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />You are snared by the words of your mouth;</para>
	<para style="q2">You are taken by the words of your mouth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />So do this, my son, and deliver yourself;</para>
	<para style="q2">For you have come into the hand of your friend:</para>
	<para style="q2">Go and humble yourself;</para>
	<para style="q2">Plead with your friend.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 132:4</char></note>Give no sleep to your eyes,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor slumber to your eyelids.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Deliver yourself like a gazelle from the hand <char style="it">of</char> <char style="it">the</char> <char style="it">hunter,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">And like a bird from the hand of the fowler.</para>
	<para style="s">The Folly of Indolence</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 12:7</char></note>Go to the ant, you sluggard!</para>
	<para style="q2">Consider her ways and be wise,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Which, having no captain,</para>
	<para style="q2">Overseer or ruler,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Provides her supplies in the summer,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> gathers her food in the harvest.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 24:33, 34</char></note>How long will you slumber, O sluggard?</para>
	<para style="q2">When will you rise from your sleep?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />A little sleep, a little slumber,</para>
	<para style="q2">A little folding of the hands to sleep—</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:4</char></note>So shall your poverty come on you like a prowler,</para>
	<para style="q2">And your need like an armed man.</para>
	<para style="s">The Wicked Man</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />A worthless person, a wicked man,</para>
	<para style="q2">Walks with a perverse mouth;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 15:12; Ps. 35:19; Prov. 10:10</char></note>He winks with his eyes,</para>
	<para style="q2">He shuffles his feet,</para>
	<para style="q2">He points with his fingers;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />Perversity <char style="it">is</char> in his heart,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 3:29; Mic. 2:1</char></note>He devises evil continually,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 6:19</char></note>He sows discord.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />Therefore his calamity shall come <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 24:22; Is. 30:13; 1 Thess. 5:3</char></note>suddenly;</para>
	<para style="q2">Suddenly he shall <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 19:11</char></note>be broken <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Chr. 36:16</char></note>without remedy.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />These six <char style="it">things</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char> hates,</para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, seven <char style="it">are</char> an abomination to Him:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 101:5; Prov. 21:4</char></note>A proud look,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 120:2; Prov. 12:22</char></note>A lying tongue,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 19:10; Prov. 28:17; Is. 1:15</char></note>Hands that shed innocent blood,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 6:5; Ps. 36:4; Prov. 24:2; Jer. 18:18; Mark 14:1, 43–46</char></note>A heart that devises wicked plans,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Kin. 5:20–27; Is. 59:7; Rom. 3:15</char></note>Feet that are swift in running to evil,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 27:12; Prov. 19:5, 9; Matt. 26:59–66</char></note>A false witness <char style="it">who</char> speaks lies,</para>
	<para style="q2">And one who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 6:14; 1 Cor. 1:11–13; (Jude 3, 4, 16–19)</char></note>sows discord among brethren.</para>
	<para style="s">Beware of Adultery</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Eph. 6:1</char></note>My son, keep your father’s command,</para>
	<para style="q2">And do not forsake the law of your mother.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 3:3</char></note>Bind them continually upon your heart;</para>
	<para style="q2">Tie them around your neck.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 3:23)</char></note>When you roam, they will lead you;</para>
	<para style="q2">When you sleep, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 2:11</char></note>they will keep you;</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">when</char> you awake, they will speak with you.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 19:8; 2 Pet. 1:19</char></note>For the commandment <char style="it">is</char> a lamp,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the law a light;</para>
	<para style="q2">Reproofs of instruction <char style="it">are</char> the way of life,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 2:16</char></note>To keep you from the evil woman,</para>
	<para style="q2">From the flattering tongue of a seductress.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 5:28</char></note>Do not lust after her beauty in your heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor let her allure you with her eyelids.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 29:3</char></note>by means of a harlot</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">man</char> <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">reduced</char> to a crust of bread;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 39:14</char></note>And an adulteress will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ezek. 13:18</char></note>prey upon his precious life.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" />Can a man take fire to his bosom,</para>
	<para style="q2">And his clothes not be burned?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" />Can one walk on hot coals,</para>
	<para style="q2">And his feet not be seared?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="29" style="v" />So <char style="it">is</char> he who goes in to his neighbor’s wife;</para>
	<para style="q2">Whoever touches her shall not be innocent.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="30" style="v" /><char style="it">People</char> do not despise a thief</para>
	<para style="q2">If he steals to satisfy himself when he is starving.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="31" style="v" />Yet <char style="it">when</char> he is found, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 22:1–4</char></note>he must restore sevenfold;</para>
	<para style="q2">He may have to give up all the substance of his house.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="32" style="v" />Whoever commits adultery with a woman <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 7:7</char></note>lacks understanding;</para>
	<para style="q2">He <char style="it">who</char> does so destroys his own soul.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="33" style="v" />Wounds and dishonor he will get,</para>
	<para style="q2">And his reproach will not be wiped away.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="34" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 27:4; Song 8:6</char></note>jealousy <char style="it">is</char> a husband’s fury;</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore he will not spare in the day of vengeance.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="35" style="v" />He will accept no recompense,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor will he be appeased though you give many gifts.</para>
	<chapter number="7" style="c" />
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />My son, keep my words,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 2:1</char></note>treasure my commands within you.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 18:5; Prov. 4:4; (Is. 55:3)</char></note>Keep my commands and live,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 32:10; Ps. 17:8; Zech. 2:8</char></note>And my law as the apple of your eye.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 6:8; Prov. 6:21</char></note>Bind them on your fingers;</para>
	<para style="q2">Write them on the tablet of your heart.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Say to wisdom, “You <char style="it">are</char> my sister,”</para>
	<para style="q2">And call understanding <char style="it">your</char> nearest kin,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 2:16; 5:3</char></note>That they may keep you from the immoral woman,</para>
	<para style="q2">From the seductress <char style="it">who</char> flatters with her words.</para>
	<para style="s">The Crafty Harlot</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />For at the window of my house</para>
	<para style="q2">I looked through my lattice,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />And saw among the simple,</para>
	<para style="q2">I perceived among the youths,</para>
	<para style="q2">A young man <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 6:32; 9:4, 16)</char></note>devoid of understanding,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Passing along the street near her corner;</para>
	<para style="q2">And he took the path to her house</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 24:15</char></note>In the twilight, in the evening,</para>
	<para style="q2">In the black and dark night.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />And there a woman met him,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">With</char> the attire of a harlot, and a crafty heart.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 9:13; 1 Tim. 5:13</char></note>She <char style="it">was</char> loud and rebellious,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Titus 2:5</char></note>Her feet would not stay at home.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />At times <char style="it">she</char> <char style="it">was</char> outside, at times in the open square,</para>
	<para style="q2">Lurking at every corner.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />So she caught him and kissed him;</para>
	<para style="q2">With an impudent face she said to him:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />“<char style="it">I</char> <char style="it">have</char> peace offerings with me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Today I have paid my vows.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />So I came out to meet you,</para>
	<para style="q2">Diligently to seek your face,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I have found you.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />I have spread my bed with tapestry,</para>
	<para style="q2">Colored coverings of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 19:9; Ezek. 27:7</char></note>Egyptian linen.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />I have perfumed my bed</para>
	<para style="q2">With myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />Come, let us take our fill of love until morning;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let us delight ourselves with love.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />For my husband <char style="it">is</char> not at home;</para>
	<para style="q2">He has gone on a long journey;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />He has taken a bag of money with him,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> will come home on the appointed day.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="21" style="v" />With <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 5:3</char></note>her enticing speech she caused him to yield,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 12:2</char></note>With her flattering lips she seduced him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />Immediately he went after her, as an ox goes to the slaughter,</para>
	<para style="q2">Or as a fool to the correction of the stocks,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" />Till an arrow struck his liver.</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Eccl. 9:12</char></note>As a bird hastens to the snare,</para>
	<para style="q2">He did not know it <char style="it">would</char> <char style="it">cost</char> his life.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="24" style="v" />Now therefore, listen to me, <char style="it">my</char> children;</para>
	<para style="q2">Pay attention to the words of my mouth:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" />Do not let your heart turn aside to her ways,</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not stray into her paths;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" />For she has cast down many wounded,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Neh. 13:26</char></note>all who were slain by her were strong <char style="it">men.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 2:18; 5:5; 9:18; (1 Cor. 6:9, 10; Rev. 22:15)</char></note>Her house <char style="it">is</char> the way to hell,</para>
	<para style="q2">Descending to the chambers of death.</para>
	<chapter number="8" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Excellence of Wisdom</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Does not <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 1:20, 21; 9:3; (1 Cor. 1:24)</char></note>wisdom cry out,</para>
	<para style="q2">And understanding lift up her voice?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />She takes her stand on the top of the high hill,</para>
	<para style="q2">Beside the way, where the paths meet.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />She cries out by the gates, at the entry of the city,</para>
	<para style="q2">At the entrance of the doors:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />“To you, O men, I call,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my voice <char style="it">is</char> to the sons of men.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />O you simple ones, understand prudence,</para>
	<para style="q2">And you fools, be of an understanding heart.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Listen, for I will speak of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 22:20</char></note>excellent things,</para>
	<para style="q2">And from the opening of my lips <char style="it">will</char> <char style="it">come</char> right things;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />For my mouth will speak truth;</para>
	<para style="q2">Wickedness <char style="it">is</char> an abomination to my lips.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />All the words of my mouth <char style="it">are</char> with righteousness;</para>
	<para style="q2">Nothing crooked or perverse <char style="it">is</char> in them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />They <char style="it">are</char> all plain to him who understands,</para>
	<para style="q2">And right to those who find knowledge.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />Receive my instruction, and not silver,</para>
	<para style="q2">And knowledge rather than choice gold;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 28:15; Ps. 19:10; 119:127; Prov. 3:14, 15; 4:5, 7; 16:16</char></note>For wisdom <char style="it">is</char> better than rubies,</para>
	<para style="q2">And all the things one may desire cannot be compared with her.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />“I, wisdom, dwell with prudence,</para>
	<para style="q2">And find out knowledge <char style="it">and</char> discretion.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 3:7; 16:6</char></note>The fear of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> to hate evil;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 2:3; (Prov. 16:17, 18; Is. 13:11)</char></note>Pride and arrogance and the evil way</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 4:24</char></note>the perverse mouth I hate.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />Counsel <char style="it">is</char> mine, and sound wisdom;</para>
	<para style="q2">I <char style="it">am</char> understanding, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Eccl. 7:19; 9:16</char></note>I have strength.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Chr. 1:10; Prov. 29:4; Dan. 2:21; (Matt. 28:18); Rom. 13:1</char></note>By me kings reign,</para>
	<para style="q2">And rulers decree justice.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />By me princes rule, and nobles,</para>
	<para style="q2">All the judges of the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 2:30; (Ps. 91:14); Prov. 4:6; (John 14:21)</char></note>I love those who love me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 2:4, 5; John 7:37; James 1:5</char></note>those who seek me diligently will find me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 3:16; (Matt. 6:33)</char></note>Riches and honor <char style="it">are</char> with me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Enduring riches and righteousness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />My fruit <char style="it">is</char> better than gold, yes, than fine gold,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my revenue than choice silver.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />I traverse the way of righteousness,</para>
	<para style="q2">In the midst of the paths of justice,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />That I may cause those who love me to inherit wealth,</para>
	<para style="q2">That I may fill their treasuries.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="22" style="v" />“The<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 28:26–28; Ps. 104:24; Prov. 3:19; (John 1:1)</char></note> <char style="sc">Lord</char> possessed me at the beginning of His way,</para>
	<para style="q2">Before His works of old.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 2:6)</char></note>I have been established from everlasting,</para>
	<para style="q2">From the beginning, before there was ever an earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" />When <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">were</char> no depths I was brought forth,</para>
	<para style="q2">When <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">were</char> no fountains abounding with water.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 15:7, 8</char></note>Before the mountains were settled,</para>
	<para style="q2">Before the hills, I was brought forth;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" />While as yet He had not made the earth or the fields,</para>
	<para style="q2">Or the primal dust of the world.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" />When He prepared the heavens, I <char style="it">was</char> there,</para>
	<para style="q2">When He drew a circle on the face of the deep,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" />When He established the clouds above,</para>
	<para style="q2">When He strengthened the fountains of the deep,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="29" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:9, 10; Job 38:8–11; Ps. 33:7; 104:9; Jer. 5:22</char></note>When He assigned to the sea its limit,</para>
	<para style="q2">So that the waters would not transgress His command,</para>
	<para style="q2">When <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 28:4, 6; Ps. 104:5</char></note>He marked out the foundations of the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="30" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(John 1:1–3, 18)</char></note>Then I was beside Him<char style="it"> as</char> a master craftsman;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 3:17)</char></note>And I was daily <char style="it">His</char> delight,</para>
	<para style="q2">Rejoicing always before Him,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="31" style="v" />Rejoicing in His inhabited world,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 16:3; John 13:1</char></note>my delight <char style="it">was</char> with the sons of men.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="32" style="v" />“Now therefore, listen to me,<char style="it"> my</char> children,</para>
	<para style="q2">For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:1, 2; 128:1; Prov. 29:18; Luke 11:28</char></note>blessed <char style="it">are</char> <char style="it">those</char> <char style="it">who</char> keep my ways.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="33" style="v" />Hear instruction and be wise,</para>
	<para style="q2">And do not disdain <char style="it">it.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="34" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 3:13, 18</char></note>Blessed is the man who listens to me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Watching daily at my gates,</para>
	<para style="q2">Waiting at the posts of my doors.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="35" style="v" />For whoever finds me finds life,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 3:4; 12:2; (John 17:3)</char></note>obtains favor from the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="36" style="v" />But he who sins against me <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 20:2</char></note>wrongs his own soul;</para>
	<para style="q2">All those who hate me love death.”</para>
	<chapter number="9" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Way of Wisdom</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Wisdom has <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 16:18; 1 Cor. 3:9, 10; Eph. 2:20–22; 1 Pet. 2:5)</char></note>built her house,</para>
	<para style="q2">She has hewn out her seven pillars;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 22:4</char></note>She has slaughtered her meat,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 23:30</char></note>She has mixed her wine,</para>
	<para style="q2">She has also furnished her table.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />She has sent out her maidens,</para>
	<para style="q2">She cries out from the highest places of the city,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />“Whoever<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 19:7</char></note> <char style="it">is</char> simple, let him turn in here!”</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">As</char> <char style="it">for</char> him who lacks understanding, she says to him,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />“Come,<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Song 5:1; Is. 55:1; (John 6:27)</char></note> eat of my bread</para>
	<para style="q2">And drink of the wine I have mixed.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Forsake foolishness and live,</para>
	<para style="q2">And go in the way of understanding.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />“He who corrects a scoffer gets shame for himself,</para>
	<para style="q2">And he who rebukes a wicked <char style="it">man</char> <char style="it">only</char> harms himself.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 15:12; Matt. 7:6</char></note>Do not correct a scoffer, lest he hate you;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 141:5; Prov. 10:8</char></note>Rebuke a wise <char style="it">man,</char> and he will love you.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Give <char style="it">instruction</char> to a wise <char style="it">man,</char> and he will be still wiser;</para>
	<para style="q2">Teach a just <char style="it">man,</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 13:12)</char></note>and he will increase in learning.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />“The<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 28:28; Ps. 111:10; Prov. 1:7</char></note> fear of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> the beginning of wisdom,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the knowledge of the Holy One <char style="it">is</char> understanding.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 3:2, 16</char></note>For by me your days will be multiplied,</para>
	<para style="q2">And years of life will be added to you.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 35:6, 7; Prov. 16:26</char></note>If you are wise, you are wise for yourself,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">if</char> you scoff, you will bear <char style="it">it</char> alone.”</para>
	<para style="s">The Way of Folly</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 7:11</char></note>A foolish woman is clamorous;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">She</char> <char style="it">is</char> simple, and knows nothing.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />For she sits at the door of her house,</para>
	<para style="q2">On a seat <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 9:3</char></note><char style="it">by</char> the highest places of the city,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />To call to those who pass by,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who go straight on their way:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />“Whoever<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 7:7, 8</char></note> <char style="it">is</char> simple, let him turn in here”;</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">as</char> <char style="it">for</char> him who lacks understanding, she says to him,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />“Stolen<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 20:17</char></note> water is sweet,</para>
	<para style="q2">And bread <char style="it">eaten</char> in secret is pleasant.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />But he does not know that <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 2:18; 7:27</char></note>the dead <char style="it">are</char> there,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">That</char> her guests <char style="it">are</char> in the depths of hell.</para>
	<chapter number="10" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Wise Sayings of Solomon</para>
	<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" />The proverbs of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 1:1; 25:1</char></note>Solomon:</para>
	<para style="q1"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 15:20; 17:21, 25; 19:13; 29:3, 15</char></note>A wise son makes a glad father,</para>
	<para style="q2">But a foolish son <char style="it">is</char> the grief of his mother.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 49:7; Prov. 11:4; 21:6; Ezek. 7:19; (Luke 12:19, 20)</char></note>Treasures of wickedness profit nothing,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Dan. 4:27</char></note>But righteousness delivers from death.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 34:9, 10; 37:25; Prov. 28:25; (Matt. 6:33)</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> will not allow the righteous soul to famish,</para>
	<para style="q2">But He casts away the desire of the wicked.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 19:15</char></note>He who has a slack hand becomes poor,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 12:24; 13:4; 21:5</char></note>the hand of the diligent makes rich.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />He who gathers in <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 6:8</char></note>summer <char style="it">is</char> a wise son;</para>
	<para style="q2">He who sleeps in harvest <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 19:26</char></note>a son who causes shame.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />Blessings <char style="it">are</char> on the head of the righteous,</para>
	<para style="q2">But violence covers the mouth of the wicked.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 112:6; Eccl. 8:10</char></note>The memory of the righteous <char style="it">is</char> blessed,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the name of the wicked will rot.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />The wise in heart will receive commands,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:10</char></note>But a prating fool will fall.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 23:4; Prov. 3:23; 28:18; Is. 33:15, 16)</char></note>He who walks with integrity walks securely,</para>
	<para style="q2">But he who perverts his ways will become known.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />He who winks with the eye causes trouble,</para>
	<para style="q2">But a prating fool will fall.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />The mouth of the righteous <char style="it">is</char> a well of life,</para>
	<para style="q2">But violence covers the mouth of the wicked.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />Hatred stirs up strife,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 17:9; (1 Cor. 13:4–7; James 5:20); 1 Pet. 4:8</char></note>love covers all sins.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />Wisdom is found on the lips of him who has understanding,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 26:3</char></note>a rod <char style="it">is</char> for the back of him who is devoid of understanding.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" />Wise <char style="it">people</char> store up knowledge,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 18:7</char></note>the mouth of the foolish <char style="it">is</char> near destruction.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" />The <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 31:24; Ps. 52:7; Prov. 18:11; (1 Tim. 6:17)</char></note>rich man’s wealth <char style="it">is</char> his strong city;</para>
	<para style="q2">The destruction of the poor <char style="it">is</char> their poverty.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />The labor of the righteous <char style="it">leads</char> to <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 6:23</char></note>life,</para>
	<para style="q2">The wages of the wicked to sin.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" />He who keeps instruction <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">in</char> the way of life,</para>
	<para style="q2">But he who refuses correction goes astray.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="18" style="v" />Whoever <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 26:24</char></note>hides hatred <char style="it">has</char> lying lips,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 15:3; 101:5</char></note>whoever spreads slander <char style="it">is</char> a fool.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 11:2; (Prov. 18:21); Eccl. 5:3</char></note>In the multitude of words sin is not lacking,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 17:27; (James 1:19; 3:2)</char></note>he who restrains his lips <char style="it">is</char> wise.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />The tongue of the righteous <char style="it">is</char> choice silver;</para>
	<para style="q2">The heart of the wicked <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">worth</char> little.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />The lips of the righteous feed many,</para>
	<para style="q2">But fools die for lack of wisdom.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="22" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 24:35; 26:12; Deut. 8:18; Ps. 37:22; Prov. 8:21</char></note>The blessing of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> makes <char style="it">one</char> rich,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He adds no sorrow with it.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="23" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 2:14; 15:21</char></note>To do evil <char style="it">is</char> like sport to a fool,</para>
	<para style="q2">But a man of understanding has wisdom.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 15:21; Prov. 1:27; Is. 66:4</char></note>The fear of the wicked will come upon him,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 145:19; Prov. 15:8; Matt. 5:6; (1 John 5:14, 15)</char></note>the desire of the righteous will be granted.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" />When the whirlwind passes by, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:9, 10</char></note>the wicked <char style="it">is</char> no <char style="it">more,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 15:5; Prov. 12:3; Matt. 7:24, 25</char></note>the righteous <char style="it">has</char> an everlasting foundation.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="26" style="v" />As vinegar to the teeth and smoke to the eyes,</para>
	<para style="q2">So <char style="it">is</char> the lazy <char style="it">man</char> to those who send him.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="27" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 9:11</char></note>The fear of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> prolongs days,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 15:32</char></note>the years of the wicked will be shortened.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" />The hope of the righteous <char style="it">will</char> <char style="it">be</char> gladness,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 8:13</char></note>expectation of the wicked will perish.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="29" style="v" />The way of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> strength for the upright,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 1:6</char></note>destruction <char style="it">will</char> <char style="it">come</char> to the workers of iniquity.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="30" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:22; Prov. 2:21</char></note>The righteous will never be removed,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the wicked will not inhabit the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="31" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:30; Prov. 10:13</char></note>The mouth of the righteous brings forth wisdom,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the perverse tongue will be cut out.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="32" style="v" />The lips of the righteous know what is acceptable,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the mouth of the wicked <char style="it">what</char> <char style="it">is</char> perverse.</para>
	<chapter number="11" style="c" />
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 19:35, 36; Deut. 25:13–16; Prov. 20:10, 23; Mic. 6:11</char></note>Dishonest scales <char style="it">are</char> an abomination to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">But a just weight <char style="it">is</char> His delight.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />When pride comes, then comes <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 16:18; 18:12; 29:23</char></note>shame;</para>
	<para style="q2">But with the humble <char style="it">is</char> wisdom.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />The integrity of the upright will guide <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 13:6</char></note>them,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the perversity of the unfaithful will destroy them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:2; Ezek. 7:19; Zeph. 1:18</char></note>Riches do not profit in the day of wrath,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 7:1</char></note>righteousness delivers from death.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />The righteousness of the blameless will direct his way aright,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the wicked will fall by his own <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 5:22</char></note>wickedness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />The righteousness of the upright will deliver them,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the unfaithful will be caught by <char style="it">their</char> lust.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />When a wicked man dies, <char style="it">his</char> expectation will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:28</char></note>perish,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the hope of the unjust perishes.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 21:18</char></note>The righteous is delivered from trouble,</para>
	<para style="q2">And it comes to the wicked instead.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />The hypocrite with <char style="it">his</char> mouth destroys his neighbor,</para>
	<para style="q2">But through knowledge the righteous will be delivered.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 28:12</char></note>When it goes well with the righteous, the city rejoices;</para>
	<para style="q2">And when the wicked perish, <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> jubilation.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />By the blessing of the upright the city is <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 14:34</char></note>exalted,</para>
	<para style="q2">But it is overthrown by the mouth of the wicked.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />He who is devoid of wisdom despises his neighbor,</para>
	<para style="q2">But a man of understanding holds his peace.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 19:16; Prov. 20:19; 1 Tim. 5:13</char></note>A talebearer reveals secrets,</para>
	<para style="q2">But he who is of a faithful spirit <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 19:11</char></note>conceals a matter.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 12:1</char></note>Where <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> no counsel, the people fall;</para>
	<para style="q2">But in the multitude of counselors <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> safety.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" />He who is <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 6:1, 2</char></note>surety for a stranger will suffer,</para>
	<para style="q2">But one who hates being surety is secure.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />A gracious woman retains honor,</para>
	<para style="q2">But ruthless <char style="it">men</char> retain riches.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 5:7; 25:34–36)</char></note>The merciful man does good for his own soul,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <char style="it">he</char> <char style="it">who</char> <char style="it">is</char> cruel troubles his own flesh.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />The wicked <char style="it">man</char> does deceptive work,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Hos. 10:12; (Gal. 6:8, 9); James 3:18</char></note>he who sows righteousness <char style="it">will</char> <char style="it">have</char> a sure reward.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />As righteousness <char style="it">leads</char> to <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:16; 12:28</char></note>life,</para>
	<para style="q2">So he who pursues evil <char style="it">pursues</char> <char style="it">it</char> to his own <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 21:16; (Rom. 6:23; James 1:15)</char></note>death.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />Those who are of a perverse heart <char style="it">are</char> an abomination to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <char style="it">the</char> blameless in their ways <char style="it">are</char> His delight.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 16:5</char></note>Though they join forces, the wicked will not go unpunished;</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 112:2; Prov. 14:26</char></note>the posterity of the righteous will be delivered.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="22" style="v" /><char style="it">As</char> a ring of gold in a swine’s snout,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">So</char> <char style="it">is</char> a lovely woman who lacks discretion.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="23" style="v" />The desire of the righteous <char style="it">is</char> only good,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> the expectation of the wicked <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:28; Rom. 2:8, 9</char></note><char style="it">is</char> wrath.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="24" style="v" />There is <char style="it">one</char> who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 112:9; Prov. 13:7; 19:17</char></note>scatters, yet increases more;</para>
	<para style="q2">And there is <char style="it">one</char> who withholds more than is right,</para>
	<para style="q2">But it <char style="it">leads</char> to poverty.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 3:9, 10; (2 Cor. 9:6, 7)</char></note>The generous soul will be made rich,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 5:7)</char></note>And he who waters will also be watered himself.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" />The people will curse <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Amos 8:5, 6</char></note>him who withholds grain,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 29:13</char></note>blessing <char style="it">will</char> <char style="it">be</char> on the head of him who sells <char style="it">it.</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="27" style="v" />He who earnestly seeks good finds favor,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Esth. 7:10; Ps. 7:15, 16; 57:6</char></note>But trouble will come to him who seeks <char style="it">evil.</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="28" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 31:24</char></note>He who trusts in his riches will fall,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 1:3; Jer. 17:8</char></note>the righteous will flourish like foliage.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="29" style="v" />He who troubles his own house <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Eccl. 5:16</char></note>will inherit the wind,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the fool <char style="it">will</char> <char style="it">be</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 14:19</char></note>servant to the wise of heart.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="30" style="v" />The fruit of the righteous <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">a</char> tree of life,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 14:25; (Dan. 12:3; 1 Cor. 9:19–22; James 5:20)</char></note>he who wins souls <char style="it">is</char> wise.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="31" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 25:29</char></note>If the righteous will be recompensed on the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">How much more the ungodly and the sinner.</para>
	<chapter number="12" style="c" />
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Whoever loves instruction loves knowledge,</para>
	<para style="q2">But he who hates correction <char style="it">is</char> stupid.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />A good <char style="it">man</char> obtains favor from the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">But a man of wicked intentions He will condemn.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />A man is not established by wickedness,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 10:25)</char></note>root of the righteous cannot be moved.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 31:23; 1 Cor. 11:7</char></note>An excellent wife <char style="it">is</char> the crown of her husband,</para>
	<para style="q2">But she who causes shame <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 14:30; Hab. 3:16</char></note>like rottenness in his bones.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />The thoughts of the righteous <char style="it">are</char> right,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> the counsels of the wicked <char style="it">are</char> deceitful.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 1:11, 18</char></note>The words of the wicked <char style="it">are,</char> “Lie in wait for blood,”</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 14:3</char></note>But the mouth of the upright will deliver them.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:35–37; Prov. 11:21; Matt. 7:24–27</char></note>The wicked are overthrown and <char style="it">are</char> no more,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the house of the righteous will stand.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />A man will be commended according to his wisdom,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 25:17; Prov. 18:3</char></note>But he who is of a perverse heart will be despised.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 13:7</char></note>Better <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">the</char> <char style="it">one</char> who is slighted but has a servant,</para>
	<para style="q2">Than he who honors himself but lacks bread.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 25:4</char></note>A righteous <char style="it">man</char> regards the life of his animal,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the tender mercies of the wicked <char style="it">are</char> cruel.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 3:19</char></note>He who tills his land will be satisfied with <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 28:19</char></note>bread,</para>
	<para style="q2">But he who follows frivolity <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 6:32</char></note><char style="it">is</char> devoid of understanding.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />The wicked covet the catch of evil <char style="it">men,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">But the root of the righteous yields <char style="it">fruit.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 18:7</char></note>The wicked is ensnared by the transgression of <char style="it">his</char> lips,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(2 Pet. 2:9)</char></note>But the righteous will come through trouble.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 13:2; 15:23; 18:20</char></note>A man will be satisfied with good by the fruit of <char style="it">his</char> mouth,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 34:11; Prov. 1:31; 24:12; (Is. 3:10, 11); Hos. 4:9</char></note>And the recompense of a man’s hands will be rendered to him.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 3:7; Luke 18:11</char></note>The way of a fool <char style="it">is</char> right in his own eyes,</para>
	<para style="q2">But he who heeds counsel <char style="it">is</char> wise.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 11:13; 29:11</char></note>A fool’s wrath is known at once,</para>
	<para style="q2">But a prudent <char style="it">man</char> covers shame.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 14:5</char></note>He <char style="it">who</char> speaks truth declares righteousness,</para>
	<para style="q2">But a false witness, deceit.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 57:4; Prov. 4:22; 15:4</char></note>There is one who speaks like the piercings of a sword,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the tongue of the wise <char style="it">promotes</char> health.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />The truthful lip shall be established forever,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 52:4, 5); Prov. 19:9</char></note>But a lying tongue <char style="it">is</char> but for a moment.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />Deceit is in the heart of those who devise evil,</para>
	<para style="q2">But counselors of peace have joy.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 91:10; Prov. 1:33; 1 Pet. 3:13</char></note>No grave trouble will overtake the righteous,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the wicked shall be filled with evil.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 6:17; 11:20; Rev. 22:15</char></note>Lying lips <char style="it">are</char> an abomination to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">But those who deal truthfully <char style="it">are</char> His delight.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="23" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 13:16</char></note>A prudent man conceals knowledge,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the heart of fools proclaims foolishness.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="24" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:4</char></note>The hand of the diligent will rule,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the lazy <char style="it">man</char> will be put to forced labor.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="25" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 15:13</char></note>Anxiety in the heart of man causes depression,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 50:4</char></note>a good word makes it glad.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="26" style="v" />The righteous should choose his friends carefully,</para>
	<para style="q2">For the way of the wicked leads them astray.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="27" style="v" />The lazy <char style="it">man</char> does not roast what he took in hunting,</para>
	<para style="q2">But diligence <char style="it">is</char> man’s precious possession.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="28" style="v" />In the way of righteousness <char style="it">is</char> life,</para>
	<para style="q2">And in <char style="it">its</char> pathway <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> no death.</para>
	<chapter number="13" style="c" />
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />A wise son <char style="it">heeds</char> his father’s instruction,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 28:14, 15</char></note>But a scoffer does not listen to rebuke.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 12:14</char></note>A man shall eat well by the fruit of <char style="it">his</char> mouth,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the soul of the unfaithful feeds on violence.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 39:1; Prov. 21:23; (James 3:2)</char></note>He who guards his mouth preserves his life,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> he who opens wide his lips shall have destruction.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:4</char></note>The soul of a lazy <char style="it">man</char> desires, and <char style="it">has</char> nothing;</para>
	<para style="q2">But the soul of the diligent shall be made rich.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />A righteous <char style="it">man</char> hates lying,</para>
	<para style="q2">But a wicked <char style="it">man</char> is loathsome and comes to shame.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 11:3, 5, 6</char></note>Righteousness guards <char style="it">him</char> <char style="it">whose</char> way is blameless,</para>
	<para style="q2">But wickedness overthrows the sinner.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 11:24; 12:9; Luke 12:20, 21)</char></note>There is one who makes himself rich, yet <char style="it">has</char> nothing;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> one who makes himself poor, yet <char style="it">has</char> great riches.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />The ransom of a man’s life <char style="it">is</char> his riches,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the poor does not hear rebuke.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />The light of the righteous rejoices,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 18:5, 6; 21:17; Prov. 24:20</char></note>But the lamp of the wicked will be put out.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />By pride comes nothing but <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:12</char></note>strife,</para>
	<para style="q2">But with the well-advised <char style="it">is</char> wisdom.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:2; 20:21</char></note>Wealth <char style="it">gained</char> <char style="it">by</char> dishonesty will be diminished,</para>
	<para style="q2">But he who gathers by labor will increase.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />Hope deferred makes the heart sick,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 13:19</char></note><char style="it">when</char> the desire comes, <char style="it">it</char> <char style="it">is</char> a tree of life.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />He who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 15:31; 2 Chr. 36:16; Is. 5:24</char></note>despises the word will be destroyed,</para>
	<para style="q2">But he who fears the commandment will be rewarded.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 6:22; 10:11; 14:27</char></note>The law of the wise <char style="it">is</char> a fountain of life,</para>
	<para style="q2">To turn <char style="it">one</char> away from <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 22:6</char></note>the snares of death.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" />Good understanding gains <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 111:10; Prov. 3:4</char></note>favor,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the way of the unfaithful <char style="it">is</char> hard.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 12:23</char></note>Every prudent <char style="it">man</char> acts with knowledge,</para>
	<para style="q2">But a fool lays open <char style="it">his</char> folly.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" />A wicked messenger falls into trouble,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 25:13</char></note>a faithful ambassador <char style="it">brings</char> health.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="18" style="v" />Poverty and shame <char style="it">will</char> <char style="it">come</char> to him who disdains correction,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 15:5, 31, 32</char></note>he who regards a rebuke will be honored.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" />A desire accomplished is sweet to the soul,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <char style="it">it</char> <char style="it">is</char> an abomination to fools to depart from evil.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="20" style="v" />He who walks with wise <char style="it">men</char> will be wise,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the companion of fools will be destroyed.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="21" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 32:10; Is. 47:11</char></note>Evil pursues sinners,</para>
	<para style="q2">But to the righteous, good shall be repaid.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="22" style="v" />A good <char style="it">man</char> leaves an inheritance to his children’s children,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 27:16, 17; Prov. 28:8; (Eccl. 2:26)</char></note>the wealth of the sinner is stored up for the righteous.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="23" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 12:11</char></note>Much food <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">in</char> the fallow <char style="it">ground</char> of the poor,</para>
	<para style="q2">And for lack of justice there is waste.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="24" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 19:18</char></note>He who spares his rod hates his son,</para>
	<para style="q2">But he who loves him disciplines him promptly.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="25" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 34:10; Prov. 10:3</char></note>The righteous eats to the satisfying of his soul,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the stomach of the wicked shall be in want.</para>
	<chapter number="14" style="c" />
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />The wise woman builds her house,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the foolish pulls it down with her hands.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />He who walks in his uprightness fears the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Rom. 2:4)</char></note>But <char style="it">he</char> <char style="it">who</char> <char style="it">is</char> perverse in his ways despises Him.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />In the mouth of a fool <char style="it">is</char> a rod of pride,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 12:6</char></note>But the lips of the wise will preserve them.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />Where no oxen <char style="it">are,</char> the trough <char style="it">is</char> clean;</para>
	<para style="q2">But much increase <char style="it">comes</char> by the strength of an ox.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />A <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rev. 1:5; 3:14</char></note>faithful witness does not lie,</para>
	<para style="q2">But a false witness will utter <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 23:1; Deut. 19:16; Prov. 6:19; 12:17</char></note>lies.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />A scoffer seeks wisdom and does not <char style="it">find</char> <char style="it">it,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 8:9; 17:24</char></note>knowledge <char style="it">is</char> easy to him who understands.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Go from the presence of a foolish man,</para>
	<para style="q2">When you do not perceive <char style="it">in</char> <char style="it">him</char> the lips of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 23:9</char></note>knowledge.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />The wisdom of the prudent <char style="it">is</char> to understand his way,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the folly of fools <char style="it">is</char> deceit.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:23</char></note>Fools mock at sin,</para>
	<para style="q2">But among the upright <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> favor.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />The heart knows its own bitterness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And a stranger does not share its joy.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 8:15</char></note>The house of the wicked will be overthrown,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the tent of the upright will flourish.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 16:25</char></note>There is a way <char style="it">that</char> <char style="it">seems</char> right to a man,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rom. 6:21</char></note>its end <char style="it">is</char> the way of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 12:15</char></note>death.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />Even in laughter the heart may sorrow,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 5:4; Eccl. 2:1, 2</char></note>the end of mirth <char style="it">may</char> <char style="it">be</char> grief.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" />The backslider in heart will be <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 1:31; 12:15</char></note>filled with his own ways,</para>
	<para style="q2">But a good man <char style="it">will</char> <char style="it">be</char> <char style="it">satisfied</char> from <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 13:2; 18:20</char></note>above.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" />The simple believes every word,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the prudent considers well his steps.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 28:28; Ps. 34:14; Prov. 22:3</char></note>A wise <char style="it">man</char> fears and departs from evil,</para>
	<para style="q2">But a fool rages and is self-confident.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />A quick-tempered <char style="it">man</char> acts foolishly,</para>
	<para style="q2">And a man of wicked intentions is hated.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />The simple inherit folly,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the prudent are crowned with knowledge.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />The evil will bow before the good,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the wicked at the gates of the righteous.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 19:7</char></note>The poor <char style="it">man</char> is hated even by his own neighbor,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the rich <char style="it">has</char> many <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 19:4</char></note>friends.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />He who despises his neighbor sins;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 112:9; (Prov. 19:17)</char></note>But he who has mercy on the poor, happy <char style="it">is</char> he.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="22" style="v" />Do they not go astray who devise evil?</para>
	<para style="q2">But mercy and truth <char style="it">belong</char> to those who devise good.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="23" style="v" />In all labor there is profit,</para>
	<para style="q2">But idle chatter <char style="it">leads</char> only to poverty.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="24" style="v" />The crown of the wise is their riches,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> the foolishness of fools <char style="it">is</char> folly.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="25" style="v" />A true witness delivers <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ezek. 3:18–21)</char></note>souls,</para>
	<para style="q2">But a deceitful <char style="it">witness</char> speaks lies.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="26" style="v" />In the fear of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> strong confidence,</para>
	<para style="q2">And His children will have a place of refuge.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 13:14</char></note>The fear of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> a fountain of life,</para>
	<para style="q2">To turn <char style="it">one</char> away from the snares of death.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="28" style="v" />In a multitude of people <char style="it">is</char> a king’s honor,</para>
	<para style="q2">But in the lack of people <char style="it">is</char> the downfall of a prince.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="29" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 16:32; 19:11; Eccl. 7:9; James 1:19</char></note><char style="it">He</char> <char style="it">who</char> <char style="it">is</char> slow to wrath has great understanding,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <char style="it">he</char> <char style="it">who</char> <char style="it">is</char> impulsive exalts folly.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="30" style="v" />A sound heart <char style="it">is</char> life to the body,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 112:10</char></note>envy <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 12:4; Hab. 3:16</char></note>rottenness to the bones.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="31" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 17:5; Matt. 25:40; 1 John 3:17</char></note>He who oppresses the poor reproaches <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 31:15; Prov. 22:2)</char></note>his Maker,</para>
	<para style="q2">But he who honors Him has mercy on the needy.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="32" style="v" />The wicked is banished in his wickedness,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 49:18; Job 13:15; (Ps. 16:11; 73:24); 2 Cor. 1:9; 5:8; (2 Tim. 4:18)</char></note>the righteous has a refuge in his death.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="33" style="v" />Wisdom rests in the heart of him who has understanding,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 12:16</char></note><char style="it">what</char> <char style="it">is</char> in the heart of fools is made known.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="34" style="v" />Righteousness exalts a <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 11:11</char></note>nation,</para>
	<para style="q2">But sin <char style="it">is</char> a reproach to <char style="it">any</char> people.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="35" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 24:45–47</char></note>The king’s favor <char style="it">is</char> toward a wise servant,</para>
	<para style="q2">But his wrath <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">against</char> him who causes shame.</para>
	<chapter number="15" style="c" />
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />A <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 25:15</char></note>soft answer turns away wrath,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 25:10</char></note>a harsh word stirs up anger.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />The tongue of the wise uses knowledge rightly,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 12:23</char></note>But the mouth of fools pours forth foolishness.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Chr. 16:9; Job 34:21; Prov. 5:21; Jer. 16:17; 32:19; Zech. 4:10; Heb. 4:13</char></note>The eyes of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">are</char> in every place,</para>
	<para style="q2">Keeping watch on the evil and the good.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />A wholesome tongue <char style="it">is</char> a tree of life,</para>
	<para style="q2">But perverseness in it breaks the spirit.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:1</char></note>A fool despises his father’s instruction,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 13:18</char></note>But he who receives correction is prudent.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" /><char style="it">In</char> the house of the righteous <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> much treasure,</para>
	<para style="q2">But in the revenue of the wicked is trouble.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />The lips of the wise disperse knowledge,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the heart of the fool <char style="it">does</char> not <char style="it">do</char> so.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 21:27; Eccl. 5:1; Is. 1:11; Jer. 6:20; Mic. 6:7</char></note>The sacrifice of the wicked <char style="it">is</char> an abomination to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the prayer of the upright <char style="it">is</char> His delight.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />The way of the wicked <char style="it">is</char> an abomination to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">But He loves him who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 21:21</char></note>follows righteousness.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 22:8</char></note>Harsh discipline <char style="it">is</char> for him who forsakes the way,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 5:12</char></note>he who hates correction will die.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 26:6; Ps. 139:8</char></note>Hell and Destruction <char style="it">are</char> before the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">So how much more <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 16:7; 2 Chr. 6:30; Ps. 44:21; Acts 1:24</char></note>the hearts of the sons of men.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 13:1; Amos 5:10; 2 Tim. 4:3</char></note>A scoffer does not love one who corrects him,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor will he go to the wise.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 12:25</char></note>A merry heart makes a cheerful countenance,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 17:22</char></note>by sorrow of the heart the spirit is broken.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" />The heart of him who has understanding seeks knowledge,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the mouth of fools feeds on foolishness.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" />All the days of the afflicted <char style="it">are</char> evil,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 17:22</char></note>But he who is of a merry heart <char style="it">has</char> a continual feast.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:16; Prov. 16:8; Eccl. 4:6; 1 Tim. 6:6</char></note>Better <char style="it">is</char> a little with the fear of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Than great treasure with trouble.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 17:1</char></note>Better <char style="it">is</char> a dinner of herbs where love is,</para>
	<para style="q2">Than a fatted calf with hatred.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 26:21</char></note>A wrathful man stirs up strife,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <char style="it">he</char> <char style="it">who</char> <char style="it">is</char> slow to anger allays contention.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 22:5</char></note>The way of the lazy <char style="it">man</char> <char style="it">is</char> like a hedge of thorns,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the way of the upright <char style="it">is</char> a highway.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:1</char></note>A wise son makes a father glad,</para>
	<para style="q2">But a foolish man despises his mother.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="21" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:23</char></note>Folly <char style="it">is</char> joy <char style="it">to</char> <char style="it">him</char> <char style="it">who</char> <char style="it">is</char> destitute of discernment,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Eph. 5:15</char></note>But a man of understanding walks uprightly.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="22" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 11:14</char></note>Without counsel, plans go awry,</para>
	<para style="q2">But in the multitude of counselors they are established.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="23" style="v" />A man has joy by the answer of his mouth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 25:11; Is. 50:4</char></note>a word <char style="it">spoken</char> in due season, how good <char style="it">it</char> <char style="it">is!</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="24" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Phil. 3:20; (Col. 3:1, 2)</char></note>The way of life <char style="it">winds</char> upward for the wise,</para>
	<para style="q2">That he may <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 14:16</char></note>turn away from hell below.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="25" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 12:7; Is. 2:11</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> will destroy the house of the proud,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 68:5, 6</char></note>He will establish the boundary of the widow.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="26" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 6:16, 18</char></note>The thoughts of the wicked <char style="it">are</char> an abomination to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:30</char></note>But the words of the pure <char style="it">are</char> pleasant.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="27" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 5:8; (Jer. 17:11)</char></note>He who is greedy for gain troubles his own house,</para>
	<para style="q2">But he who hates bribes will live.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="28" style="v" />The heart of the righteous <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Pet. 3:15</char></note>studies how to answer,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the mouth of the wicked pours forth evil.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="29" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 10:1; 34:16</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> far from the wicked,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 145:18; (James 5:16)</char></note>He hears the prayer of the righteous.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="30" style="v" />The light of the eyes rejoices the heart,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> a good report makes the bones healthy.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="31" style="v" />The ear that hears the rebukes of life</para>
	<para style="q2">Will abide among the wise.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="32" style="v" />He who disdains instruction despises his own soul,</para>
	<para style="q2">But he who heeds rebuke gets understanding.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="33" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 1:7</char></note>The fear of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> the instruction of wisdom,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 18:12</char></note>before honor <char style="it">is</char> humility.</para>
	<chapter number="16" style="c" />
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />The <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 10:23</char></note>preparations of the heart <char style="it">belong</char> to man,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 10:19</char></note>But the answer of the tongue <char style="it">is</char> from the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />All the ways of a man <char style="it">are</char> pure in his own <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 21:2</char></note>eyes,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the <char style="sc">Lord</char> weighs the spirits.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:5; Prov. 3:6; (1 Pet. 5:7)</char></note>Commit your works to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And your thoughts will be established.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />The <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 43:7; Rom. 11:36</char></note><char style="sc">Lord</char> has made all for Himself,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 21:30; (Rom. 9:22)</char></note>Yes, even the wicked for the day of doom.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 6:17; 8:13</char></note>Everyone proud in heart <char style="it">is</char> an abomination to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Though</char> <char style="it">they</char> <char style="it">join</char> forces, none will go unpunished.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Dan. 4:27; Luke 11:41</char></note>In mercy and truth</para>
	<para style="q2">Atonement is provided for iniquity;</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 8:13; 14:16</char></note>by the fear of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">one</char> departs from evil.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />When a man’s ways please the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">He makes even his enemies to be at peace with him.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:16; Prov. 15:16</char></note>Better <char style="it">is</char> a little with righteousness,</para>
	<para style="q2">Than vast revenues without justice.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 19:21</char></note>A man’s heart plans his way,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:23; Prov. 20:24; Jer. 10:23</char></note>But the <char style="sc">Lord</char> directs his steps.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />Divination <char style="it">is</char> on the lips of the king;</para>
	<para style="q2">His mouth must not transgress in judgment.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 19:36</char></note>Honest weights and scales <char style="it">are</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char>’s;</para>
	<para style="q2">All the weights in the bag <char style="it">are</char> His work.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><char style="it">It</char> <char style="it">is</char> an abomination for kings to commit wickedness,</para>
	<para style="q2">For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 25:5</char></note>a throne is established by righteousness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 14:35</char></note>Righteous lips <char style="it">are</char> the delight of kings,</para>
	<para style="q2">And they love him who speaks <char style="it">what</char> <char style="it">is</char> right.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />As messengers of death <char style="it">is</char> the king’s wrath,</para>
	<para style="q2">But a wise man will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 25:15</char></note>appease it.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />In the light of the king’s face <char style="it">is</char> life,</para>
	<para style="q2">And his favor <char style="it">is</char> like a <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Zech. 10:1</char></note>cloud of the latter rain.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 8:10, 11, 19</char></note>How much better to get wisdom than gold!</para>
	<para style="q2">And to get understanding is to be chosen rather than silver.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" />The highway of the upright <char style="it">is</char> to depart from evil;</para>
	<para style="q2">He who keeps his way preserves his soul.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="18" style="v" />Pride <char style="it">goes</char> before destruction,</para>
	<para style="q2">And a haughty spirit before a fall.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />Better <char style="it">to</char> <char style="it">be</char> of a humble spirit with the lowly,</para>
	<para style="q2">Than to divide the spoil with the proud.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="20" style="v" />He who heeds the word wisely will find good,</para>
	<para style="q2">And whoever <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 34:8; Jer. 17:7</char></note>trusts in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, happy <char style="it">is</char> he.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="21" style="v" />The wise in heart will be called prudent,</para>
	<para style="q2">And sweetness of the lips increases learning.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="22" style="v" />Understanding <char style="it">is</char> a wellspring of life to him who has it.</para>
	<para style="q2">But the correction of fools <char style="it">is</char> folly.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="23" style="v" />The heart of the wise teaches his mouth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And adds learning to his lips.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="24" style="v" />Pleasant words <char style="it">are</char> <char style="it">like</char> a honeycomb,</para>
	<para style="q2">Sweetness to the soul and health to the bones.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="25" style="v" />There is a way <char style="it">that</char> <char style="it">seems</char> right to a man,</para>
	<para style="q2">But its end <char style="it">is</char> the way of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 14:12</char></note>death.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="26" style="v" />The person who labors, labors for himself,</para>
	<para style="q2">For his <char style="it">hungry</char> mouth drives <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Eccl. 6:7; John 6:35)</char></note>him <char style="it">on.</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="27" style="v" />An ungodly man digs up evil,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">it</char> <char style="it">is</char> on his lips like a burning <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(James 3:6)</char></note>fire.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" />A perverse man sows strife,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 17:9</char></note>a whisperer separates the best of friends.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="29" style="v" />A violent man entices his neighbor,</para>
	<para style="q2">And leads him in a way <char style="it">that</char> <char style="it">is</char> not good.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="30" style="v" />He winks his eye to devise perverse things;</para>
	<para style="q2">He purses his lips <char style="it">and</char> brings about evil.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="31" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 20:29</char></note>The silver-haired head <char style="it">is</char> a crown of glory,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">If</char> it is found in the way of righteousness.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="32" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 14:29; 19:11</char></note><char style="it">He</char> <char style="it">who</char> <char style="it">is</char> slow to anger <char style="it">is</char> better than the mighty,</para>
	<para style="q2">And he who rules his spirit than he who takes a city.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="33" style="v" />The lot is cast into the lap,</para>
	<para style="q2">But its every decision <char style="it">is</char> from the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<chapter number="17" style="c" />
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Better <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 15:17</char></note>a dry morsel with quietness,</para>
	<para style="q2">Than a house full of feasting <char style="it">with</char> strife.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />A wise servant will rule over <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:5</char></note>a son who causes shame,</para>
	<para style="q2">And will share an inheritance among the brothers.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />The refining pot <char style="it">is</char> for silver and the furnace for gold,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 29:17; Ps. 26:2; Prov. 15:11; Jer. 17:10; (Mal. 3:3)</char></note>But the <char style="sc">Lord</char> tests the hearts.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />An evildoer gives heed to false lips;</para>
	<para style="q2">A liar listens eagerly to a spiteful tongue.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 14:31</char></note>He who mocks the poor reproaches his Maker;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 31:29; Prov. 24:17; Obad. 12; 1 Cor. 13:6</char></note>He who is glad at calamity will not go unpunished.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 127:3; 128:3)</char></note>Children’s children <char style="it">are</char> the crown of old men,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the glory of children <char style="it">is</char> their father.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Excellent speech is not becoming to a fool,</para>
	<para style="q2">Much less lying lips to a prince.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />A present <char style="it">is</char> a precious stone in the eyes of its possessor;</para>
	<para style="q2">Wherever he turns, he prospers.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 10:12; 1 Cor. 13:5–7; James 5:20)</char></note>He who covers a transgression seeks love,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 16:28</char></note>he who repeats a matter separates friends.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:17; (Mic. 7:9)</char></note>Rebuke is more effective for a wise <char style="it">man</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Than a hundred blows on a fool.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />An evil <char style="it">man</char> seeks only rebellion;</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore a cruel messenger will be sent against him.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />Let a man meet <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 17:8; Hos. 13:8</char></note>a bear robbed of her cubs,</para>
	<para style="q2">Rather than a fool in his folly.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />Whoever <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 109:4, 5; Jer. 18:20; Rom. 12:17; 1 Thess. 5:15; (1 Pet. 3:9)</char></note>rewards evil for good,</para>
	<para style="q2">Evil will not depart from his house.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" />The beginning of strife <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">like</char> releasing water;</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 20:3; 1 Thess. 4:11)</char></note>stop contention before a quarrel starts.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 23:7; Prov. 24:24; Is. 5:23</char></note>He who justifies the wicked, and he who condemns the just,</para>
	<para style="q2">Both of them alike <char style="it">are</char> an abomination to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />Why <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">there</char> in the hand of a fool the purchase price of wisdom,</para>
	<para style="q2">Since <char style="it">he</char> <char style="it">has</char> no heart <char style="it">for</char> <char style="it">it?</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ruth 1:16; Prov. 18:24</char></note>A friend loves at all times,</para>
	<para style="q2">And a brother is born for adversity.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 6:1</char></note>A man devoid of understanding shakes hands in a pledge,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> becomes surety for his friend.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" />He who loves transgression loves strife,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 16:18</char></note>he who exalts his gate seeks destruction.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="20" style="v" />He who has a deceitful heart finds no good,</para>
	<para style="q2">And he who has <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">James 3:8</char></note>a perverse tongue falls into evil.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="21" style="v" />He who begets a scoffer <char style="it">does</char> <char style="it">so</char> to his sorrow,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the father of a fool has no joy.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="22" style="v" />A <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 12:25; 15:13, 15</char></note>merry heart does good, <char style="it">like</char> medicine,</para>
	<para style="q2">But a broken spirit dries the bones.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="23" style="v" />A wicked <char style="it">man</char> accepts a bribe behind the back</para>
	<para style="q2">To pervert the ways of justice.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="24" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Eccl. 2:14</char></note>Wisdom <char style="it">is</char> in the sight of him who has understanding,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the eyes of a fool <char style="it">are</char> on the ends of the earth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="25" style="v" />A <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:1; 15:20; 19:13</char></note>foolish son <char style="it">is</char> a grief to his father,</para>
	<para style="q2">And bitterness to her who bore him.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="26" style="v" />Also, to punish the righteous <char style="it">is</char> not good,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Nor</char> to strike princes for <char style="it">their</char> uprightness.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="27" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:19; James 1:19</char></note>He who has knowledge spares his words,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> a man of understanding is of a calm spirit.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="28" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 13:5</char></note>Even a fool is counted wise when he holds his peace;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">When</char> he shuts his lips, <char style="it">he</char> <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">considered</char> perceptive.</para>
	<chapter number="18" style="c" />
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />A man who isolates himself seeks his own desire;</para>
	<para style="q2">He rages against all wise judgment.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />A fool has no delight in understanding,</para>
	<para style="q2">But in expressing his <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Eccl. 10:3</char></note>own heart.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />When the wicked comes, contempt comes also;</para>
	<para style="q2">And with dishonor <char style="it">comes</char> reproach.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:11</char></note>The words of a man’s mouth <char style="it">are</char> deep waters;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(James 3:17)</char></note>The wellspring of wisdom <char style="it">is</char> a flowing brook.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><char style="it">It</char> <char style="it">is</char> not good to show partiality to the wicked,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Or</char> to overthrow the righteous in <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 19:15; Deut. 1:17; 16:19; Ps. 82:2; Prov. 17:15</char></note>judgment.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />A fool’s lips enter into contention,</para>
	<para style="q2">And his mouth calls for blows.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 64:8; 140:9; Prov. 10:14</char></note>A fool’s mouth <char style="it">is</char> his destruction,</para>
	<para style="q2">And his lips <char style="it">are</char> the snare of his <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Eccl. 10:12</char></note>soul.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 12:18</char></note>The words of a talebearer <char style="it">are</char> like tasty trifles,</para>
	<para style="q2">And they go down into the inmost body.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />He who is slothful in his work</para>
	<para style="q2">Is a brother to him who is a great destroyer.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />The name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> a strong <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 22:2, 3, 33; Ps. 18:2; 61:3; 91:2; 144:2</char></note>tower;</para>
	<para style="q2">The righteous run to it and are safe.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />The rich man’s wealth <char style="it">is</char> his strong city,</para>
	<para style="q2">And like a high wall in his own esteem.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 15:33; 16:18</char></note>Before destruction the heart of a man is haughty,</para>
	<para style="q2">And before honor <char style="it">is</char> humility.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />He who answers a matter before he hears <char style="it">it,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">It <char style="it">is</char> folly and shame to him.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" />The spirit of a man will sustain him in sickness,</para>
	<para style="q2">But who can bear a broken spirit?</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" />The heart of the prudent acquires knowledge,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the ear of the wise seeks knowledge.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 32:20, 21; 1 Sam. 25:27; Prov. 17:8; 21:14</char></note>A man’s gift makes room for him,</para>
	<para style="q2">And brings him before great men.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" />The first <char style="it">one</char> to plead his cause <char style="it">seems</char> right,</para>
	<para style="q2">Until his neighbor comes and examines him.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="18" style="v" />Casting <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 16:33)</char></note>lots causes contentions to cease,</para>
	<para style="q2">And keeps the mighty apart.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" />A brother offended <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">harder</char> <char style="it">to</char> <char style="it">win</char> than a strong city,</para>
	<para style="q2">And contentions <char style="it">are</char> like the bars of a castle.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 12:14; 14:14</char></note>A man’s stomach shall be satisfied from the fruit of his mouth;</para>
